{
  "answer": "In *Sayed Ki Loh-e-Turbat* (\"The Epitaph of the Sayed\"), Iqbal uses apostrophe via **prosopopoeia** (personification of the inanimate), allowing the tombstone of Sayyid Ahmed Khan to address the living reader directly as \"O you\" (a mortal soul still confined by life), conveying the reformer's enduring wisdom on leadership, unity, and fearless expression.[^1] This indirect strategy animates the absent/dead figure to critique and inspire the Muslim community from beyond the grave, emphasizing legacy and posthumous vitality.\n\nBy contrast, in *Sach keh doon ae Brahman! gar tu bura na maane* (\"O Brahmin, if you will not take offense\"), Iqbal employs **direct apostrophe**, hailing an unnamed living Brahmin interlocutor to bluntly declare the obsolescence of \"ancient idols\" and urge transcendence of religious division toward universal love.[^2] This immediate, confrontational address targets a contemporaneous Hindu figure (potentially symbolic of broader stagnation), fostering dialogue across communal lines in the poet's own voice.\n\nThe strategies thus differ in **agency and temporality**: the tomb's voice bridges death and life for intra-community renewal, while the direct call to the Brahmin seeks interfaith provocation in the present.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 38 (\"Sayed Ki Loh-e-Turbat\"), [paras. p-b2c140, p-3ab597, p-f55cb3](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/38-sayed-ki-loh-e-turbat/translation/#p-b2c140).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 36 (\"Sach keh doon ae Brahman! gar tu bura na maane\"), [para. p-752d60](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/36-sach-keh-doon-ae-brahman-gar-tu-bura-na-maane/translation/#p-752d60).\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 36, [paras. p-752d60–p-c536e2](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/36-sach-keh-doon-ae-brahman-gar-tu-bura-na-maane/translation/#p-752d60); ch. 38 [paras. p-3ab597–p-f55cb3](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/38-sayed-ki-loh-e-turbat/translation/#p-3ab597).",
